SADC to Hold Summit on Security in Maputo
MAPUTO , February 26 ( Xinhua ) -- The Southern African Development Community ( SADC ) is to hold a special summit on regional security and politics here on March 2.
A news release from the Mozambican Presidential Office said Thursday that the one-day summit would be chaired by Nelson Mandela , South African President as the chairman and , Joaquim Chissano , Mozambican President as the Vice-Chairman .
SADC is a 14-member regional organization aimed at regional economic integrity .
